For web-scale apps that do not require schema, but where each table must have a primary key, that are designed to scale outusing distributed hardware clusters.
NoSQL databases such as DynamoDB can manage structured or semi-structured data. 
The advantage of NoSQL databases are that rows and elements can be easily added or removed from the table entry. It is beneficial for low-latency, high-traffic queries.
NoSQL scales well because of its scema flexibility allowing it to store complex hierachical data within a single item, and related items may be stored close together on the same table via the composite key design

RedShift is also NoSQL and is generally used for OLAP systems.


